=Description=

"The Community Chartering group has been set up to advocate Community Charters, and the community chartering process, as a new model for community engagement around essential rights and responsibilities. Our network comprises expertise in planning and environmental law, group facilitation and consensus building, as well as on-the-ground community stakeholder groups.  

Our mission is to support communities who feel disempowered by local planning processes, are threatened by harmful developments, and / or who wish to ensure that their health, wellbeing, economy and natural environment are bequeathed to the next generation in a better state than they were received. We aim to work with you to determine the best possible outcome and future for your environment and homes.  We are not aligned with any NGO or political group."


